# Web Shopping Agent

The **Web Shopping Agent** is a smart conversational bot designed to enhance your online shopping experience. It understands user queries, provides personalized product recommendations, and streamlines the shopping process with ease.

---

## ğŸš€ Quick Start Guide

Follow these simple steps to set up and run the Web Shopping Agent on your local machine.

### 1. Clone the Repository
Clone the project repository to your local system:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/pulsebot-ai/web-shopping-agent.git
cd web-shopping-agent
```

### 2. Install Dependencies
Ensure you have Python installed, then install the required dependencies:

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 3. Set Up Environment Variables
Configure the application by creating and updating your `.env` file:

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

Add your API keys and other parameters to the `.env` file to ensure proper functionality.

### 4. Run the Application
Start the application using Uvicorn:

```bash
uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000
```

### 5. Access the Application
Open your browser and navigate to:

```
http://localhost:8000
```

